g_{ab} \in GL
 \chi_a \circ \chi_b^{-1}(p, k) = \chi_a \left(\sum k_{i_1 \dots i_s, j_1 \dots j_r} \dfrac{\p}{\p x^{i_1}_b} \otimes \dots \otimes \dfrac{\p}{\p x^{i_s}_b} \otimes dx^{j_1}_b \otimes \dots \otimes dx^{j_r}_b \right) = \chi_a \left(\sum k_{i_1 \dots i_s, j_1 \dots j_r} \underbrace{\dfrac{\p x^{p_1}_a}{\p x^{i_1}_b} \dots \dfrac{\p x^{p_s}_a}{\p x^{i_s}_b}  \dfrac{\p x^{j_1}_b}{\p x^{q_1}_a} \dots \dfrac{\p x^{j_r}_b}{\p x^{q_r}_a}} \dfrac{\p}{\p x^{p_1}_a} \otimes \dots \otimes \dfrac{\p}{\p x^{p_s}_a} \otimes dx^{q_1}_a \otimes \dots \otimes dx^{q_r}_a \right).
